Defendant Daniel J Robinson in court with attorney Ryan J. Harrington.  Lindsey Hirt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Harrington makes statements.  Defendant's mother makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following:  Count #1. 

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
10 months Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 3 days).  
Term of Probation: 2 Years
Early release from probation after 18 months if agent approves
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
No contact with Salty Toad or intentional contact with the officer. 
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
Perform  40 hours of community service;
Maintain employment or school;
Condition Time: 90 days Huber with  NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS  STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
COSTS:  $268.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $250.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.  
Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
